This topic describes how to install and configure IBM WebSphere Liberty for VMware Tanzu.

##<a id='install'></a> Install and Configure IBM WebSphere Liberty for VMware Tanzu

To install the IBM WebSphere Liberty for VMware Tanzu file on the Ops Manager Installation Dashboard, do the following:

1. Download the product file from Pivotal Network.

1. Navigate to the Ops Manager Installation Dashboard and click **Import a Product** to upload the product file. 

1. Under the **Import a Product** button, click **+** next to the version number of IBM WebSphere Liberty for VMware Tanzu. 
This adds the tile to your staging area.

1. Click the newly added **IBM WebSphere Liberty for VMware Tanzu** tile.

1. Click **Buildpack Settings** and enter the position for the buildpack installed by the tile.
   This sets the order of the buildpack relative to the other buildpacks in the detection priority list.
   For more information, see [Buildpack Detection](https://docs.pivotal.io/pivotalcf/buildpacks/detection.html#buildpack-detection). 
    <%= image_tag('buildpack_settings.png') %>

1. Click **Save**.

1. Return to the Ops Manager Installation Dashboard and click **Apply changes** to install IBM WebSphere Liberty for VMware Tanzu tile.

